      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Policy: add sandbox posture conformance checks",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nAdds config-level Policy conformance checks for sandbox posture:\n\n```jsonc\n{\n  \"sandbox\": {\n    \"requireMode\": [\"all\", \"non-main\"],\n    \"allowBackends\": [\"docker\", \"openshell\"],\n    \"docker\": {\n      \"denyNetworks\": [\"host\", \"container:*\"],\n      \"requireBindMode\": \"ro\",\n      \"denyDockerSocketBinds\": true,\n      \"denyUnconfinedProfiles\": true\n    },\n    \"browser\": {\n      \"requireCdpSourceRange\": true\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThis stays in the config-conformance lane: it checks authored OpenClaw config and reports drift through policy/doctor findings. It does not inspect live containers, host filesystem permissions, process state, or network state, and it does not add runtime enforcement.\n\nThe PR also extends the named `scopes.<scopeName>` overlay model from #85817 so sandbox posture can be scoped to explicit runtime `agentIds`. Scope names are descriptive buckets; matching uses normalized runtime ids. The same agent may be in multiple scopes when each scope governs different fields, or when a repeated field is equally or more restrictive according to policy metadata:\n\n```jsonc\n{\n  \"scopes\": {\n    \"release-workspace\": {\n      \"agentIds\": [\"release-agent\"],\n      \"agents\": {\n        \"workspace\": { \"allowedAccess\": [\"none\", \"ro\"] }\n      }\n    },\n    \"release-sandbox\": {\n      \"agentIds\": [\"release-agent\"],\n      \"sandbox\": {\n        \"requireMode\": [\"all\"],\n        \"allowBackends\": [\"docker\"]\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## Verification\n\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --threads=1 extensions/policy/src/doctor/register.ts extensions/policy/src/doctor/register.test.ts docs/cli/policy.md docs/plan/policy-agent-scoped-overlays.md docs/plugins/reference/policy.md`\n- `pnpm exec oxlint extensions/policy/src/doctor/register.ts extensions/policy/src/doctor/register.test.ts`\n- `pnpm docs:check-mdx docs/cli/policy.md docs/plugins/reference/policy.md docs/plan/policy-agent-scoped-overlays.md`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/policy/src/doctor/register.test.ts extensions/policy/src/cli.test.ts -- --reporter=verbose --testTimeout=30000` -> 2 files, 193 tests passed\n- `git diff --check`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Policy can now express sandbox posture requirements for mode, backend, Docker network, Docker bind mode, Docker socket binds, Docker unconfined profiles, sandbox browser CDP source range, and agent-scoped sandbox overlays.\n\nReal environment tested: WSL Ubuntu 24.04 checkout at `/root/src/openclaw-policy-sandbox-posture`, rebased on current main, using focused policy doctor and CLI tests.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: see Verification commands above.\n\nEvidence after fix: focused tests cover failing sandbox config, passing sandbox config, inherited defaults, per-agent sandbox posture, scoped `agentIds` overlays, and strictness metadata for scoped sandbox rules.\n\nObserved result after fix: the focused policy test suite passes with the new `scopes.<scopeName>.sandbox.*` behavior and the touched code and docs use the current top-level named scope syntax.\n\nWhat was not tested: live Docker/browser containers were not launched because this PR intentionally checks config conformance only, not runtime sandbox behavior.\r\n\r\n\n",
